3 K-core

k-core is a maximal subset of vertices such that each is connected to at least k others in the subset.R has a function wich calculates the coreness for each vertex.The coreness of a vertex is k if it belongs to the k-core but not to the (k+1)-core.

3.1 Finding maximum k-core and pick out it on graph

coreness <- graph.coreness(confianca)
V(confianca)$coreness<-graph.coreness(confianca)
max_cor <- max(coreness)
max_cor <- max(coreness)

3.2 Max Coreness

max_cor
## [1] 17

3.3 Heat map for coreness

#Defining Heat Color
color_bar <- heat.colors(max_cor) 
V(confianca)$color_bar<-color_bar[coreness]

set.seed(123)
#Plotting based only on degree measures 
edge.start <- ends(confianca, es=E(confianca), names=F)[,1]

# Fixing ego
minC <- rep(-Inf, vcount(confianca))
maxC <- rep(Inf, vcount(confianca))
minC[1] <- maxC[1] <- 0
co <- layout_with_fr(confianca, niter=10^4, minx=minC, maxx=maxC,miny=minC, maxy=maxC, weights = E(confianca)$weight)

#Plotting
plot(confianca, 
     layout=co,
     edge.color=V(confianca)$color_bar[edge.start],
     edge.arrow.size=degree(confianca)/10000,
     edge.width=E(confianca)$weight/10*mean(E(confianca)$weight),
     edge.curved = TRUE,
     vertex.color = color_bar[coreness],
     vertex.size=(degree(confianca)+10)/5,
     vertex.frame.color="black",
     vertex.label.color="black",
     vertex.label=get.vertex.attribute(confianca,"LABEL_COR"),
     vertex.label.cex=(degree(confianca)+0.01)/400,
     vertex.label.dist=0,
     rescale=F,
     xlim=range(co[,1]), 
     ylim=range(co[,2])
     )
axis(1)
axis(2)

#Solving Problems with legend rendering 
a<-V(confianca)$coreness
b<-V(confianca)$color_bar
c<-table(a,b)
d<-as.data.frame(c)
e<-subset(d, d$Freq>0)
f<-t(e$a)
g<-t(e$b)

#Adding Legend
legend(x=range(co[,1])[2], 
       y=range(co[,2])[2],
       legend=as.character(f),
       pch=21,
       col = "#777777", 
       pt.bg=as.character(g),
       pt.cex=2,
       bty="n", 
       ncol=1,
       lty=1,
       cex = .3)

#Adding Title
  title("Coreness Colored Graph - 31_CONFIANÇA", sub = "Source: from authors ", cex = .5)
  text( 
    x=range(co[,1])[1],
    y=range(co[,2])[1], 
      labels =     sprintf("Mean Coreness: %.2f\nMax Coreness: %.2f",
     mean(graph.coreness(confianca)), 
     max(graph.coreness(confianca))
             )
       )
